Troubleshooting
Issue: Scripts fail with permission errors

Solution: Ensure scripts are executable with chmod +x
Check file ownership with ls -l
Issue: Services won't start after drill

Check configuration files for corruption
Review service logs: journalctl -u nginx -n 50
Restore from backup if needed
Issue: Disk fill script fills entire disk

Stop script immediately: pkill -f disk-fill
Remove test files: sudo rm -rf /tmp/disk-fill-test
Add safety checks to limit fill amount
Issue: Can't access logs

Check log directory permissions
Verify log rotation hasn't moved files
Use sudo if accessing system logs
